    "branch_rationale": "Q_top is the integer winding charge defined as the sum of triangle Wilson-loop windings on the Xi-active sub-complex; the vortex set is nodes participating in any triangle with discrete Wilson-loop winding |w| >= 0.25. Both definitions are algebraic and branch-independent: no chirality-flippable coefficient (alpha_xi, gamma, beta_pi, D_Omega, eps_sync) enters the construction, so the bundle's branch tag holds across all regimes. The diagnostic spans the canonical lattice ladder from N=18 to N=512, including the regenerated N=256 12-seed run and the N=512 12-seed run. Q_top is consumed by matter-localisation studies (defect-matter overlap analyses) but is itself branch-blind by construction.",
